author: Inside Edition
description: The time has come for many to get rid of their Christmas trees. Inside Edition's Alison Hall decided to feed her tree to the goats at Cropsey Farms in New City, New York. The goats eat all the needles and even the bark. On average, each goat eats one tree a day. There are other easy ways to dispose of a Christmas tree. Many municipalities have drop off areas for recycling. Depending on where you live, you can put your Christmas tree on the curb and the sanitation department will take it away.
title: Ways To Dispose Of Your Christmas Tree

author: Inside Edition
description: A grandmother and her grandkids got lost during a hike, triggering a massive search and rescue operation. Tonda Michelin, 14-year-old Melody, 11-year-old Dale, and a third grandchild went hiking in Caesar's Head State Park in South Carolina. A fog moved in and it started to rain. Suddenly, Tonda says, the trail petered out. They were able to call 911 on the one cellphone among them. Searcher Joey Oberman heard the family's dog, Coco, barking. The family was airlifted out.
title: Grandma And Grandkids Rescued After Getting Lost During Hike

author: Inside Edition
description: Mickey Rourke is blasting a GoFundMe site that has been set up to help the actor. He claimed the GoFundMe was set up without his knowledge, even though it says it was created by a person on his management team "with Mickey's full permission." Two weeks ago,  Rourke was photographed retrieving groceries from outside his Los Angeles rental as he faced eviction from his home for non-payment of $59,100 in back rent. Then, two days ago, he was photographed moving out.
title: Mickey Rourke Blasts GoFundMe Page Set Up To Help Him

author: Inside Edition
description: A shadowy figure is being called a "person of interest" by police in connection with the brutal double murder of a dentist and his wife. A man was seen walking in an alley behind the townhouse where 37-year-old Spencer Tepe and his wife Monique were found shot to death. Authorities say the video was captured on a Nest camera in an alley in the 3-hour window when police believe the murders were committed. Forensics expert Joseph Scott Morgan analyzed the video for Inside Edition.
title: Police Seek Person Of Interest In Double Murder Of Dentist And Wife

author: Inside Edition
description: The first images of Venezuelan President Nicolas Maduro after his capture are generating lots of chatter on social media. He had three outfit changes on his journey to the US. President Donald Trump hailed Maduro's capture, and it seemed like he confirmed reports that the video of Maduro dancing in the days leading up to the raid really bugged him. Not everyone on team Trump is celebrating. Conservative podcaster Megyn Kelly says she's withholding her verdict on Operation Absolute Resolve.
title: Maduro's Outfit Changes Generate Social Media Chatter

author: Inside Edition
description: Dr. Kerri Turner Bryant is married to Georgia pastor and activist Jamal Bryant. Her black lace and strapless gown gave the illusion that it was sheer, but it had a nude lining. The dress worn at a fundraising event has become the center of an ongoing controversy. The outfit received thousands of comments both for and against it. On New Year's Eve, Pastor Bryant talked about it from the pulpit at New Birth Missionary Baptist Church in Atlanta.
title: Pastor Jamal Bryant Speaks Out About Wife's Controversial Dress

author: Inside Edition
description: A pack of mountain lions is responsible for the fatal New Year's Day attack of 46-year-old ultramarathon runner Kristen Marie Kovatch. She was on a solo hike near Rocky Mountain National Park in Colorado when they lunged at her. Three months ago, Mary Crone encountered a mountain lion on a hike with her 13-year-old terrier. Inside Edition got some tips on what to do to stay safe if you are confronted by a mountain lion.
title: Pack Of Mountain Lions Kill Ultramarathoner During Hike

author: Inside Edition
description: The Gwinnett County Police Department says it was responding to a complaint of a stolen car. Cops soon found the car, but the suspect was not inside. Witnesses told police he ran off, but he wasn't exactly discreet. Cops say multiple reports started coming in from residents about a man running around nearly nude, with only a table cloth covering himself. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Suspected Car Thief Runs Around Neighborhood Wearing Only Tablecloth

author: Inside Edition
description: Officer bodycam captured police in Cortland, Ohio rescuing a man from a car that had caught fire.
title: Cops Pull Injured Man From Burning Car #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A Catholic influencer is mourning the loss of his 5-year-old son who died from complications of influenza. Paul J. Kim had been updating his more than 390,000 followers on Instagram daily since his son, Micah, was rushed to the hospital on December 21. At a hospital, Micah was placed on life support where he fought for more than a week, while his family and their supporters prayed for his recovery. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Catholic Influencer Announces Death Of 5-Year-Old Son From Influenza

author: Inside Edition
description: A dog was abandoned and left to die in a trash compactor. It happened outside a Los Angeles church. Police say the puppy had been dropped into a trash compactor that automatically crushed its contents to make room for more garbage. A passerby reported hearing whimpering coming from inside the trash can. Sgt Nick Beerling arrived just in time. The 18-year veteran of the Gardena Police Department named the pup "Norm," after the street where he was found.
title: Police Officer Adopts Puppy Abandoned In Trash Compactor

author: Inside Edition
description: Michelle Newton's father, Joe, never stopped looking for her.
title: Woman Reunites With Long-Lost Family #shorts
